latestPosts.caption:
Week 28 of 2025 was pretty usual. Spent most of it working and went to the gym after the longest time. 

Also tried 2 new restaurants and absolutely loved them! I’ve been enjoying Asian food, especially hotpots and Japanese, a lot lately. Also took an IELTS because my job needs one. 

Here’s some pictures from the week 
1. From a brunch I enjoyed 
2. Yummiest hotpot ever. Lotus stem is my new favourite 😻 
3. It rained and the sky looked gorgeous 
4. Celebrated my friend finally kick-starting his startup journey @zuppnow 🎂
5. More pretty skies ☁️☁️
6. Flowers I got this week 🥰
7. Went to watch Jurassic World 🦕
8. Took an IELTS after a 2 hour prep (lol, I was surprised at how easy it was)
9. A new restaurant I tried and really liked 
10. Worked on a collab reel 

#aksundayrecap2025 #aksundayrecap 

What’s new with you guys??

Week 27 of 2025 was a rather eventful one, with loads of socialising. I was visiting my team in Pune and we had the best time getting to know each other. 

I also went for a karaoke night, the first one I’ve ever been to and it was so much fun, definitely need to do it more often. 

Here’s some pictures from the week:
1. A morning hike in the hills 🏔️
2. The Pune office building at blue hour 
3. Some food I really enjoyed 
4. Went to watch the materialists 
5. Had brunch with bestie 🥙
6. Only the best mangoes I’ve ever had 🥭
7. Went for a swim after the longest time 
8. View from the office in Pune 
9. Went to watch F1 movie
10. The moody monsoon skies ⛈️

Went for the most amazing massage I’ve ever gotten at Spa Ceylon and absolutely loved the experience. 

They have 3 outlets and I went to the one in Weligama. Everything smelt amazing and I loved the products they used. 

10/10 recommend

#getyourguide #getyourguidecommunity #spaexperience #weligama #ahangama #mirissa #colombosrilanka @getyourguidecommunity @getyourguide

Just wanted to circle back on this trend and share a quick reminder that I do in fact speak consulting too :)

Also, there are no free trips or vacations. Nothing in this world is free unless it’s a gift :P
Gotta do what you gotta do 🤡

This little town was nothing short of a slice of heaven on earth and I was truly blessed with a perfect day.

The 14 hour day trip was extremely worth the early start and I was honestly surprised at how much we did in just one day. 

The driver was super nice and every single location was more beautiful than the other. 🥹

I stayed in the south (in Mirissa) for the entirety of my trip and went to Ella for a day trip but you can also stay there for a couple days and truly soak in all the beauty. 

You can book this experience on getyourguide like I did :)
